{"paragraphs":[{"cues":[{"time":1995,"text":"Every weekend for as long\nas I can remember,"},{"time":5746,"text":"my father would get up on a Saturday,"},{"time":8597,"text":"put on a worn sweatshirt"},{"time":11163,"text":"and he'd scrape away"},{"time":12342,"text":"at the squeaky old wheel\nof a house that we lived in."},{"time":15681,"text":"I wouldn't even call it restoration;"},{"time":17493,"text":"it was a ritual, catharsis."},{"time":19906,"text":"He would spend all year\nscraping paint with this old heat gun"},{"time":23290,"text":"and a spackle knife,"},{"time":24558,"text":"and then he would repaint\nwhere he scraped,"},{"time":26659,"text":"only to begin again the following year."},{"time":29052,"text":"Scraping and re-scraping,\npainting and repainting:"},{"time":32688,"text":"the work of an old house\nis never meant to be done."}]},{"cues":[{"time":37589,"text":"The day my father turned 52,\nI got a phone call."},{"time":40945,"text":"My mother was on the line"},{"time":42391,"text":"to tell me that doctors had found\na lump in his stomach --"},{"time":46153,"text":"terminal cancer, she told me,"},{"time":48196,"text":"and he had been given\nonly three weeks to live."}]},{"cues":[{"time":52269,"text":"I immediately moved home\nto Poughkeepsie, New York,"},{"time":55814,"text":"to sit with my father on death watch,"},{"time":58246,"text":"not knowing what the next days\nwould bring us."},{"time":61529,"text":"To keep myself distracted,"},{"time":62920,"text":"I rolled up my sleeves,"},{"time":64698,"text":"and I went about finishing\nwhat he could now no longer complete --"},{"time":68627,"text":"the restoration of our old home."}]},{"cues":[{"time":71666,"text":"When that looming three-week deadline came"},{"time":74731,"text":"and then went,"},{"time":75913,"text":"he was still alive."},{"time":77904,"text":"And at three months,"},{"time":79410,"text":"he joined me."},{"time":80901,"text":"We gutted and repainted the interior."},{"time":83600,"text":"At six months, the old windows\nwere refinished,"},{"time":86918,"text":"and at 18 months,"},{"time":88237,"text":"the rotted porch was finally replaced."}]},{"cues":[{"time":91575,"text":"And there was my father,"},{"time":93427,"text":"standing with me outside,\nadmiring a day's work,"},{"time":96704,"text":"hair on his head, fully in remission,"},{"time":99727,"text":"when he turned to me and he said,"},{"time":101985,"text":"\"You know, Michael,"},{"time":103166,"text":"this house saved my life.\""}]},{"cues":[{"time":106967,"text":"So the following year, I decided\nto go to architecture school."}]},{"cues":[{"time":112167,"text":"(Laughter)"}]},{"cues":[{"time":113929,"text":"But there, I learned\nsomething different about buildings."},{"time":117073,"text":"Recognition seemed to come"},{"time":118728,"text":"to those who prioritized\nnovel and sculptural forms,"},{"time":122303,"text":"like ribbons, or ..."},{"time":125514,"text":"pickles?"}]},{"cues":[{"time":126697,"text":"(Laughter)"}]},{"cues":[{"time":130866,"text":"And I think this\nis supposed to be a snail."}]},{"cues":[{"time":134530,"text":"Something about this bothered me."},{"time":136971,"text":"Why was it that the best architects,\nthe greatest architecture --"},{"time":140938,"text":"all beautiful and visionary\nand innovative --"},{"time":144078,"text":"is also so rare,"},{"time":146273,"text":"and seems to serve so very few?"},{"time":149715,"text":"And more to the point:"},{"time":151236,"text":"With all of this creative talent,\nwhat more could we do?"}]},{"cues":[{"time":156556,"text":"Just as I was about to start\nmy final exams,"},{"time":158889,"text":"I decided to take a break\nfrom an all-nighter"},{"time":162018,"text":"and go to a lecture by Dr. Paul Farmer,"},{"time":165514,"text":"a leading health activist\nfor the global poor."},{"time":168534,"text":"I was surprised to hear a doctor\ntalking about architecture."},{"time":172340,"text":"Buildings are making\npeople sicker, he said,"},{"time":174846,"text":"and for the poorest in the world,"},{"time":176663,"text":"this is causing epidemic-level problems."},{"time":179918,"text":"In this hospital in South Africa,"},{"time":181577,"text":"patients that came in\nwith, say, a broken leg,"},{"time":183785,"text":"to wait in this unventilated hallway,"},{"time":186405,"text":"walked out with a multidrug-resistant\nstrand of tuberculosis."},{"time":191294,"text":"Simple designs for infection control\nhad not been thought about,"},{"time":194942,"text":"and people had died because of it."}]},{"cues":[{"time":198014,"text":"\"Where are the architects?\" Paul said."},{"time":201692,"text":"If hospitals are making people sicker,"},{"time":203717,"text":"where are the architects and designers"},{"time":205645,"text":"to help us build and design\nhospitals that allow us to heal?"}]},{"cues":[{"time":212486,"text":"That following summer,"},{"time":214150,"text":"I was in the back of a Land Rover\nwith a few classmates,"},{"time":216976,"text":"bumping over the mountainous\nhillside of Rwanda."},{"time":220964,"text":"For the next year, I'd be living in Butaro\nin this old guesthouse,"},{"time":224957,"text":"which was a jail after the genocide."},{"time":228967,"text":"I was there to design and build\na new type of hospital"},{"time":232912,"text":"with Dr. Farmer and his team."},{"time":235965,"text":"If hallways are making patients sicker,"},{"time":238123,"text":"what if we could design a hospital\nthat flips the hallways on the outside,"},{"time":241901,"text":"and makes people walk in the exterior?"},{"time":244243,"text":"If mechanical systems rarely work,"},{"time":246636,"text":"what if we could design a hospital\nthat could breathe"},{"time":249243,"text":"through natural ventilation,"},{"time":251143,"text":"and meanwhile reduce\nits environmental footprint?"}]},{"cues":[{"time":254309,"text":"And what about the patients' experience?"},{"time":256889,"text":"Evidence shows\nthat a simple view of nature"},{"time":259229,"text":"can radically improve health outcomes,"},{"time":261752,"text":"So why couldn't we design a hospital"},{"time":263838,"text":"where every patient\nhad a window with a view?"},{"time":266575,"text":"Simple, site-specific designs\ncan make a hospital that heals."}]},{"cues":[{"time":272764,"text":"Designing it is one thing;"},{"time":274571,"text":"getting it built, we learned,\nis quite another."}]},{"cues":[{"time":277619,"text":"We worked with Bruce Nizeye,"},{"time":280327,"text":"a brilliant engineer,"},{"time":281864,"text":"and he thought about\nconstruction differently"},{"time":284012,"text":"than I had been taught in school."},{"time":286458,"text":"When we had to excavate\nthis enormous hilltop"},{"time":288806,"text":"and a bulldozer was expensive\nand hard to get to site,"},{"time":291765,"text":"Bruce suggested doing it by hand,"},{"time":294309,"text":"using a method in Rwanda called \"Ubudehe,\""},{"time":298007,"text":"which means \"community works\nfor the community.\""},{"time":301082,"text":"Hundreds of people came\nwith shovels and hoes,"},{"time":305008,"text":"and we excavated that hill"},{"time":306819,"text":"in half the time and half\nthe cost of that bulldozer."},{"time":311328,"text":"Instead of importing furniture,\nBruce started a guild,"},{"time":314292,"text":"and he brought in\nmaster carpenters to train others"},{"time":316723,"text":"in how to make furniture by hand."},{"time":318501,"text":"And on this job site,"},{"time":320095,"text":"15 years after the Rwandan genocide,"},{"time":324326,"text":"Bruce insisted that we bring on\nlabor from all backgrounds,"},{"time":327955,"text":"and that half of them be women."}]},{"cues":[{"time":330302,"text":"Bruce was using\nthe process of building to heal,"},{"time":332971,"text":"not just for those who were sick,"},{"time":334980,"text":"but for the entire community as a whole."},{"time":339086,"text":"We call this the locally fabricated\nway of building, or \"lo-fab,\""},{"time":343965,"text":"and it has four pillars:"},{"time":346984,"text":"hire locally,"},{"time":348182,"text":"source regionally,"},{"time":350111,"text":"train where you can"},{"time":351555,"text":"and most importantly,"},{"time":353143,"text":"think about every design decision\nas an opportunity"},{"time":356729,"text":"to invest in the dignity\nof the places where you serve."},{"time":361219,"text":"Think of it like the local food movement,"},{"time":364073,"text":"but for architecture."},{"time":365741,"text":"And we're convinced\nthat this way of building"},{"time":367968,"text":"can be replicated across the world,"},{"time":369930,"text":"and change the way we talk about\nand evaluate architecture."}]},{"cues":[{"time":375405,"text":"Using the lo-fab way of building,"},{"time":377231,"text":"even aesthetic decisions\ncan be designed to impact people's lives."},{"time":381762,"text":"In Butaro, we chose to use\na local volcanic stone"},{"time":384488,"text":"found in abundance within the area,"},{"time":386540,"text":"but often considered\na nuisance by farmers,"},{"time":388601,"text":"and piled on the side of the road."},{"time":390671,"text":"We worked with these masons\nto cut these stones"},{"time":393179,"text":"and form them into the walls\nof the hospital."},{"time":396394,"text":"And when they began on this corner"},{"time":398615,"text":"and wrapped around the entire hospital,"},{"time":402283,"text":"they were so good at putting\nthese stones together,"},{"time":404829,"text":"they asked us if they could take down\nthe original wall and rebuild it."},{"time":408465,"text":"And you see what is possible."},{"time":411467,"text":"It's beautiful."},{"time":413794,"text":"And the beauty, to me,"},{"time":415697,"text":"comes from the fact that I know\nthat hands cut these stones,"},{"time":419435,"text":"and they formed them into this thick wall,"},{"time":422444,"text":"made only in this place\nwith rocks from this soil."}]},{"cues":[{"time":428107,"text":"When you go outside today\nand you look at your built world,"},{"time":432973,"text":"ask not only:"},{"time":434178,"text":"\"What is the environmental footprint?\" --\nan important question --"},{"time":437428,"text":"but what if we also asked,"},{"time":438726,"text":"\"What is the human handprint\nof those who made it?\""}]},{"cues":[{"time":443427,"text":"We started a new practice\nbased around these questions,"},{"time":447095,"text":"and we tested it around the world."},{"time":450467,"text":"Like in Haiti,"},{"time":451642,"text":"where we asked if a new hospital\ncould help end the epidemic of cholera."},{"time":456755,"text":"In this 100-bed hospital,"},{"time":458418,"text":"we designed a simple strategy"},{"time":460117,"text":"to clean contaminated medical waste\nbefore it enters the water table,"},{"time":464601,"text":"and our partners at Les Centres GHESKIO"},{"time":466633,"text":"are already saving lives because of it."}]},{"cues":[{"time":469187,"text":"Or Malawi:"},{"time":470406,"text":"we asked if a birthing center\ncould radically reduce"},{"time":473659,"text":"maternal and infant mortality."},{"time":475892,"text":"Malawi has one of the highest rates\nof maternal and infant death"},{"time":479169,"text":"in the world."},{"time":480410,"text":"Using a simple strategy\nto be replicated nationally,"},{"time":483757,"text":"we designed a birthing center"},{"time":486001,"text":"that would attract women\nand their attendants"},{"time":488333,"text":"to come to the hospital earlier\nand therefore have safer births."}]},{"cues":[{"time":492569,"text":"Or in the Congo, where we asked"},{"time":494267,"text":"if an educational center\ncould also be used"},{"time":496539,"text":"to protect endangered wildlife."},{"time":498745,"text":"Poaching for ivory and bushmeat"},{"time":500354,"text":"is leading to global epidemic,\ndisease transfer and war."},{"time":503925,"text":"In one of the hardest-to-reach\nplaces in the world,"},{"time":507171,"text":"we used the mud and the dirt\nand the wood around us"},{"time":510121,"text":"to construct a center"},{"time":511809,"text":"that would show us ways to protect\nand conserve our rich biodiversity."}]},{"cues":[{"time":517526,"text":"Even here in the US,"},{"time":519155,"text":"we were asked to rethink"},{"time":520442,"text":"the largest university for the deaf\nand hard of hearing in the world."},{"time":524844,"text":"The deaf community, through sign language,"},{"time":527124,"text":"shows us the power\nof visual communication."},{"time":529558,"text":"We designed a campus\nthat would awaken the ways"},{"time":531834,"text":"in which we as humans all communicate,"},{"time":533907,"text":"both verbally and nonverbally."}]},{"cues":[{"time":537729,"text":"And even in Poughkeepsie, my hometown,"},{"time":540986,"text":"we thought about old\nindustrial infrastructure."},{"time":544196,"text":"We wondered:"},{"time":545497,"text":"Could we use arts and culture\nand design to revitalize this city"},{"time":550084,"text":"and other Rust Belt cities\nacross our nation,"},{"time":552730,"text":"and turn them into centers\nfor innovation and growth?"},{"time":556121,"text":"In each of these projects,\nwe asked a simple question:"},{"time":560045,"text":"What more can architecture do?"},{"time":562681,"text":"And by asking that question,"},{"time":564630,"text":"we were forced to consider\nhow we could create jobs,"},{"time":568396,"text":"how we could source regionally"},{"time":570831,"text":"and how we could invest\nin the dignity of the communities"},{"time":574081,"text":"in which we serve."}]},{"cues":[{"time":575959,"text":"I have learned"},{"time":577943,"text":"that architecture can be\na transformative engine for change."}]},{"cues":[{"time":585117,"text":"About a year ago, I read an article"},{"time":588567,"text":"about a tireless and intrepid\ncivil rights leader"},{"time":593328,"text":"named Bryan Stevenson."}]},{"cues":[{"time":596423,"text":"(Applause)"}]},{"cues":[{"time":602249,"text":"And Bryan had a bold architectural vision."},{"time":605983,"text":"He and his team had been documenting"},{"time":608596,"text":"the over 4,000 lynchings\nof African-Americans"},{"time":612264,"text":"that have happened in the American South."},{"time":614889,"text":"And they had a plan to mark every county\nwhere these lynchings occurred,"},{"time":619723,"text":"and build a national memorial\nto the victims of lynching"},{"time":623136,"text":"in Montgomery, Alabama."}]},{"cues":[{"time":625879,"text":"Countries like Germany and South Africa"},{"time":629880,"text":"and, of course, Rwanda,"},{"time":631073,"text":"have found it necessary to build memorials"},{"time":634169,"text":"to reflect on the atrocities\nof their past,"},{"time":637032,"text":"in order to heal their national psyche."},{"time":640044,"text":"We have yet to do this\nin the United States."}]},{"cues":[{"time":644679,"text":"So I sent a cold email\nto info@equaljusticeintiative.org:"},{"time":651338,"text":"\"Dear Bryan,\" it said,"},{"time":654102,"text":"\"I think your building project"},{"time":655762,"text":"is maybe the most important\nproject we could do in America"},{"time":658741,"text":"and could change the way\nwe think about racial injustice."},{"time":662640,"text":"By any chance,"},{"time":664648,"text":"do you know who will design it?\""}]},{"cues":[{"time":666593,"text":"(Laughter)"}]},{"cues":[{"time":668784,"text":"Surprisingly, shockingly,"},{"time":671547,"text":"Bryan got right back to me,"},{"time":672885,"text":"and invited me down to meet\nwith his team and talk to them."},{"time":676763,"text":"Needless to say,\nI canceled all my meetings"},{"time":678839,"text":"and I jumped on a plane\nto Montgomery, Alabama."},{"time":681203,"text":"When I got there,"},{"time":682797,"text":"Bryan and his team picked me up,\nand we walked around the city."},{"time":686305,"text":"And they took the time to point out"},{"time":688656,"text":"the many markers that have\nbeen placed all over the city"},{"time":691701,"text":"to the history of the Confederacy,"},{"time":694169,"text":"and the very few that mark\nthe history of slavery."}]},{"cues":[{"time":698420,"text":"And then he walked me to a hill."},{"time":700828,"text":"It overlooked the whole city."},{"time":702934,"text":"He pointed out the river\nand the train tracks"},{"time":705188,"text":"where the largest domestic\nslave-trading port in America"},{"time":707907,"text":"had once prospered."},{"time":709115,"text":"And then to the Capitol rotunda,"},{"time":710757,"text":"where George Wallace\nhad stood on its steps"},{"time":712853,"text":"and proclaimed, \"Segregation forever.\""},{"time":716205,"text":"And then to the very hill below us."},{"time":718080,"text":"He said, \"Here we will build\na new memorial"},{"time":721421,"text":"that will change the identity\nof this city and of this nation.\""}]},{"cues":[{"time":726855,"text":"Our two teams have worked\ntogether over the last year"},{"time":730333,"text":"to design this memorial."},{"time":735184,"text":"The memorial will take us on a journey"},{"time":738836,"text":"through a classical,\nalmost familiar building type,"},{"time":741934,"text":"like the Parthenon\nor the colonnade at the Vatican."},{"time":746994,"text":"But as we enter,"},{"time":748345,"text":"the ground drops below us\nand our perception shifts,"},{"time":752330,"text":"where we realize that these columns\nevoke the lynchings,"},{"time":756448,"text":"which happened in the public square."},{"time":759005,"text":"And as we continue,"},{"time":760345,"text":"we begin to understand the vast number"},{"time":763464,"text":"of those who have yet to be put to rest."},{"time":766481,"text":"Their names will be engraved\non the markers that hang above us."},{"time":772202,"text":"And just outside will be a field\nof identical columns."},{"time":776973,"text":"But these are temporary columns,\nwaiting in purgatory,"},{"time":780796,"text":"to be placed in the very counties\nwhere these lynchings occurred."},{"time":786124,"text":"Over the next few years,"},{"time":788520,"text":"this site will bear witness,"},{"time":791060,"text":"as each of these markers is claimed"},{"time":793322,"text":"and visibly placed in those counties."},{"time":796258,"text":"Our nation will begin to heal\nfrom over a century of silence."}]},{"cues":[{"time":803799,"text":"When we think about\nhow it should be built,"},{"time":805876,"text":"we were reminded of Ubudehe,"},{"time":808700,"text":"the building process\nwe learned about in Rwanda."},{"time":811562,"text":"We wondered if we could fill\nthose very columns"},{"time":814130,"text":"with the soil from the sites\nof where these killings occurred."},{"time":819218,"text":"Brian and his team have begun\ncollecting that soil"},{"time":822940,"text":"and preserving it in individual jars"},{"time":825748,"text":"with family members, community\nleaders and descendants."},{"time":829890,"text":"The act of collecting soil itself"},{"time":834148,"text":"has lead to a type of spiritual healing."},{"time":837545,"text":"It's an act of restorative justice."}]},{"cues":[{"time":840844,"text":"As one EJI team member noted"},{"time":843422,"text":"in the collection of the soil\nfrom where Will McBride was lynched,"},{"time":848231,"text":"\"If Will McBride left one drop of sweat,"},{"time":851388,"text":"one drop of blood,"},{"time":853173,"text":"one hair follicle --"},{"time":854964,"text":"I pray that I dug it up,"},{"time":856609,"text":"and that his whole body\nwould be at peace.\""}]},{"cues":[{"time":862683,"text":"We plan to break ground\non this memorial later this year,"},{"time":865968,"text":"and it will be a place to finally speak\nof the unspeakable acts"},{"time":870437,"text":"that have scarred this nation."}]},{"cues":[{"time":874380,"text":"(Applause)"}]},{"cues":[{"time":885245,"text":"When my father told me\nthat day that this house --"},{"time":888706,"text":"our house --"},{"time":889885,"text":"had saved his life,"},{"time":891970,"text":"what I didn't know"},{"time":893306,"text":"was that he was referring\nto a much deeper relationship"},{"time":896582,"text":"between architecture and ourselves."},{"time":899649,"text":"Buildings are not simply\nexpressive sculptures."},{"time":903019,"text":"They make visible our personal\nand our collective aspirations"},{"time":907141,"text":"as a society."},{"time":909177,"text":"Great architecture can give us hope."},{"time":913162,"text":"Great architecture can heal."}]},{"cues":[{"time":916478,"text":"Thank you very much."}]},{"cues":[{"time":917719,"text":"(Applause)"}]}]}